"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448365","Department of Health","false","2016-02-01","<p>NHS England aims to finalise and publish its thematic review of how the mental health needs of children and young people in vulnerable groups have been addressed as part of the overall Local Transformation Plan analysis by 30 April 2016. A number of thematic reviews have been commissioned as part of the overall analysis of the Local Transformation Plans. One of these thematic reviews focuses on vulnerable groups of children and young people, which will include children who have been abused.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","24630","2016-02-01T12:55:18.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448365/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448365/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-27","Mental Health Services: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant the Answer of 18 December 2015 to Question 20074, on mental health services: children, when he expects that the thematic review will be (a) finished and (b) published.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","24629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448366","Department of Health","false","2016-02-01","<p>NHS England aims to finalise and publish its thematic review of how the mental health needs of children and young people in vulnerable groups have been addressed as part of the overall Local Transformation Plan analysis by 30 April 2016. A number of thematic reviews have been commissioned as part of the overall analysis of the Local Transformation Plans. One of these thematic reviews focuses on vulnerable groups of children and young people, which will include children who have been abused.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","24629","2016-02-01T12:55:18.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448366/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448366/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448366/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-27","Mental Health Services: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 18 December 2015 to Question 20074, on mental health services: children, whether it is planned that the thematic review will consider children who have been abused as a specific theme separate to children and young people more generally.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","24630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448367","Department of Health","false","2016-02-01","<p>The Local Government Association (LGA) has published a spreadsheet containing a list of all 123 Local Transformation Plans (LTPs), the clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) they cover, and links to where the plans are published locally, where the LGA is aware of this. The list can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/camhs" target="_blank">www.local.gov.uk/camhs</a></p><p> </p><p>All LTPs were required to be published locally by 31 December 2015, and CCGs have been asked to provide details of where they are published to NHS England as part of the quarterly monitoring process, which will next be collected in February.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-02-01T16:18:11.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448367/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448367/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448367/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-27","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 22 January 2016 to Question 23217, which clinical commissioning groups have provided details of where their plans are published; and where such transformation plans can be accessed.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","24631"
