"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448381","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>The Home Office has made no assessment of the effect of the visa refund fee scheme because it is operated by Visit Britain on behalf of the Department for Culture, Media and Sport.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-02-02T15:28:39.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448381/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448381/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448381/answer/previousversion/42441","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-27","Visas: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made on the effect of the visa refund fee scheme on the number of Chinese people visiting the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","24381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448382","Home Office","false","2016-02-03","<p>We believe approximately 800 UK linked individuals of national security concern have travelled to take part in the Syrian conflict since it began. Of those who are known to have travelled, about half have returned.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-02-03T16:28:12.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448382/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448382/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-27","Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the total number of people from the UK who have joined Daesh.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","24419"
