"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448402","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-29","<p>Although youth offending is down, reoffending rates are far too high and the care and supervision of young offenders is custody is not good enough.</p><p>That is why the Justice Secretary has asked Charlie Taylor to conduct a review of youth justice. He will report back later this year with recommendations on how to improve the treatment of young people in our care.</p><p> </p><p>The Table below is based on quarterly information provided to the Youth Justice Board by Barnardo’s and includes all safeguarding issues raised with a Barnardo’s advocate. When a safeguarding issue is raised with a Barnardo’s advocate, they will make a referral through the establishment’s safeguarding process, which is agreed with the Local Authority Designated Officer (LADO). The YJB monitors continually check whether referrals are being made when they should be. Cases can also be directly referred to the LADO by any member of staff, a Barnardo’s advocate, or a YJB monitor.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 1: Number of safeguarding incidents reported to Barnardo’s advocates in STCs and under-18 YOIs: July 2013-June 2015</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>July 2013 to June 2014</p></td><td><p>July 2014 to June 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>STCs</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>26</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Under-18 YOIs</p></td><td><p>172</p></td><td><p>208</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><ul><li>The July 2014 to June 2015 data include Hassockfield STC and Hindley YOI which were decommissioned part way through this period</li></ul>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-03-29T14:36:51.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448402/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448402/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448402/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-01-27","Youth Custody: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many incidents relating to safety of children in secure training centres and young offender institutions have been raised by Barnardo's advocates with (a) Youth Justice Board monitors and (b) local children's safeguarding boards in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","24386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448403","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-02","<p>This information is not held.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-02-02T17:56:07.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448403/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448403/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448403/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-01-27","Employment Tribunals Service: Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many employment tribunal (ET) cases involved employees and employers from the maritime industry in each year since 2008-09; and what proportion of the total number of ET cases such cases were in each such year.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","24447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448404","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-03","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold the number of people released from custodial sentences as a result of wrongful convictions in England and Wales. Obtaining this information would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-02-03T15:42:17.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448404/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448404/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448404/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-01-27","Miscarriages of Justice: Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been released from custodial sentences as a result of wrongful convictions in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","24436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448405","Leader of the House","false","2016-02-03","<p>The date for the next State Opening of Parliament will be announced by Written Statement in the usual way.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2016-02-03T11:08:43.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448405/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448405/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-01-27","Opening of Parliament","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what date is planned for the State Opening of Parliament in 2016.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","24624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448406","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>I have agreed to undertake a thorough assessment of the request that this group are offered right of abode in the United Kingdom, based on their employment in Hong Kong. This is under consideration.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","24491","2016-02-02T15:24:35.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448406/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448406/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448406/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-27","Right of Abode: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy to grant right of abode in this country to former British-Hong Kong servicemen.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","24490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448407","Home Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>I have agreed to undertake a thorough assessment of the request that this group are offered right of abode in the United Kingdom, based on their employment in Hong Kong. This is under consideration.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","24490","2016-02-02T15:24:35.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448407/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448407/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-27","Right of Abode: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if the Prime Minister will issue a response to (a) Early Day Motion 722, Right of abode for former British-Hong Kong servicemen and (b) petitions on this subject presented at 10 Downing Street on 5 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","24491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448408","Scotland Office","false","2016-02-05","<p>UK and Scottish Government officials have regular discussions regarding immigration matters, including screening of asylum seekers in Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-02-05T12:41:43.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448408/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448408/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-27","Asylum: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the Scottish Government on the screening of asylum seekers in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","24613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448409","Scotland Office","false","2016-02-04","<p>In-work and out of work working age benefits are available for those who have not yet reached State Pension age.</p><p> </p><p>The women affected by the Pensions Act 2011 will reach State Pension age after the introduction of the new State Pension, which will be more generous for those historically worse off under the current system.</p><p> </p><p>Further, a £1 billion concession was made, limiting the delay that anyone would experience to their State Pension age to 18 months, relative to the Pensions Act 1995 timetable. This mitigated the effect of the changes for those most affected by the Pensions Act 2011.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-02-04T14:12:57.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448409/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448409/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448409/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-27","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, if he will take steps to provide compensation for people in Scotland who have lost out financially as a result of the increase in the women's pension age.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","24526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448410","Scotland Office","false","2016-02-02","<p>I last met Citizens Advice Scotland on 3 August 2015 in Edinburgh. We discussed a range of matters, including the implementation of the Smith Commission Agreement.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-02-02T11:42:49.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448410/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448410/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448410/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-27","Citizens Advice Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, when Ministers in his Department last met Citizens Advice Scotland; what was discussed at that meeting; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","24612"
