ishment (a) Aldermaston and (b) Burghfield.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","24295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447857","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-03","<p>Project Mensa was approved in May 2011 with an in-service date between 2016 and 2020.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-02-03T16:13:03.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447857/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447857/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447857/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","AWE Burghfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he expects the Mensa warhead assembly and disassembly facility at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Burghfield to begin operation.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","24296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447858","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-29","<br /><p>The number of weapons fired by each weapon type in each country during the period requested up to 24 January 2016 is shown below:</p><br /><p>RAF Weapon Usage on Op SHADER in Iraq and Syria</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Weapon Type</p></td><td><p>Number of weapons fired at targets in Iraq From September 2014</p></td><td><p>Number of weapons fired at targets in Syria From 2 December 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hellfire</p></td><td><p>311</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dual Mode Seeker Brimstone</p></td><td><p>117</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Paveway IV</p></td><td><p>540</p></td><td><p>34</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The Ministry of Defence provides a regular update on airstrikes at http//www.gov.uk/government/news/update-air-strikes-in-Iraq</p><br /><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-29T14:04:05.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447858/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447858/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447858/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times (a) Brimstone missiles, (b) Hellfire missiles and (c) Paveway IV guided bombs have been deployed against targets in (i) Iraq since September 2014 and (ii) Syria since December 2015.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447859","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-03","<p>Ships' complements are not fixed; they vary, even across a class, depending on equipment fits and in response to specific tasking.</p><p> </p><p>HMS OCEAN has a complement of 380 when in her normal operating role; however, this would have varied during her deployment on COUGAR 15 as personnel embarked and disembarked dependent on the activity. The Embarked Military Force (Royal Marines and Aviation Group personnel) was in the region of 620.</p><p> </p><p>Similarly, the number and type of helicopters embarked varied depending on the activity. At points during the deployment, HMS OCEAN carried the following helicopters:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Chinook CH47</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apache</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wildcat</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Merlin Mk2</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Osprey MV 22 (US Marine Corps)</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-03T16:41:36.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447859/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447859/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447859/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","HMS Ocean: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total crew complement of HMS Ocean was on its most recent deployment; of what the Embarked Military Forces she carried consisted; and how many helicopters of which type she carried.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447860","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-03","<p>The Ministry of Defence manages a wide range of assets to support the UK Armed Forces. A list of equipment due to be decommissioned in the next 12 months is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>However, the following major equipment platforms are planned to be taken out of service in 2016:</p><p>Sea King Mk3, 3a, 4 and 5;</p><p>RFA Black Rover - Royal Fleet Auxiliary Fleet Support Tanker.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-03T16:02:27.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447860/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447860/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447860/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","Defence Equipment: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which assets his Department plans to decommission over the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447861","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-01","<p>The cost of decommissioning HMS OCEAN is yet to be determined.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-01T17:15:32.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447861/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447861/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447861/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","HMS Ocean: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his current estimate is of the cost of decommissioning HMS Ocean.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447862","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-28","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 7 January 2016 to Question 20545 to the hon. Member for Bridgend (Mrs Moon).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-28T16:44:31.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447862/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447862/answer","20160107_20545_Shipbuilding[1].docx","20160107 - QnA extract on Shipbuilding","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447862/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","Shipping: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the Government plans to publish its shipbuilding strategy.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447863","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-01","<p>Ministry of Defence equipment disposal receipts for the last six full financial years are provided in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Net Receipts £ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>28.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>46.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>229.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>39.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>44.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>32.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-01T17:39:14.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447863/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447863/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447863/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","Defence Equipment: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much income his Department has received from the sale of surplus equipment in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447864","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>HMS OCEAN deployed away from UK waters twice in 2015. In July she participated in Exercise BALTOPS, a major Allied naval exercise in the Baltic Sea, and between September and December she was deployed on COUGAR 15, the annual deployment of the UK's high readiness maritime Joint Expeditionary Force.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-02T16:00:46.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447864/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447864/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447864/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","HMS Ocean: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times HMS Ocean has been deployed in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","24283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447865","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>There are 4,920 permanent staff and 890 contractors employed at the Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE). These figures represent full time equivalent staff, rounded to the nearest ten.</p><p>Contractors working at AWE but employed by sub-contractor companies are not included as this information is not held centrally.</p><p>Over the next three years, staffing levels will depend on programme demand.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-02-02T15:47:37.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447865/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447865/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","AWE: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) permanent staff, (b) temporary staff and (c) contractors are employed at the Atomic Weapons Establishment; and how many such staff he expects to be employed at that Establishment in each of the next three years.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","24292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447866","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-02","<p>There are 209 contractors and 78 AWE personnel working on decommissioning projects, including demolition, at the Atomic Weapons Establishment</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-02T15:41:58.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447866/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447866/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","AWE: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) AWE personnel and (b) contractors are working on legacy decommissioning projects at the Atomic Weapons Establishment.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","24293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447867","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-03","<p>The overall cost to the UK of procuring the Mk4A component was an element of the estimated future costs of the Atomic Weapons Establishment as set out in chapter five of the White Paper 'The Future of the United Kingdom's Nuclear Deterrent' (Cmd 6994), published in December 2006.</p><p>Further details on the costs of the Mk4A programme are being withheld for the purpose of safeguarding national security.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-02-03T16:42:14.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447867/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447867/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-26","Trident Missiles: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the costs are of the Mk4A Trident warhead modification programme for each year of the Nuclear Warhead Capability Sustainment Programme.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","24294"
