"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447928","Home Office","false","2016-02-03","<p>The Home Office does not hold data centrally on the number of people employed by the Metropolitan Police Service who were former employees of News International.</p><p>Individual police forces in England and Wales are responsible for deciding when and how they run their recruitment and selection processes.</p><p>Decisions on whether to recruit individuals are for the chief officer of the police force concerned.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-02-03T14:53:12.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447928/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447928/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/447928/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-26","Metropolitan Police: News International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people employed by the Metropolitan Police Service are former employees of News International.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","24348"
